text: Dabou is a port city in southern Ivory Coast. It is the capital of both the Lagunes District and the Grands-Ponts Region. It is also the capital of and a sub-prefecture of the Dabou Department. Dabou is also a commune. In 2021, 138,083 people lived there. Dabou Airport is in the town. Category:Cities in Ivory Coast
title: Dabou
